      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed from at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on QoI (hemolysis index) for all assessed operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mesh refinement study performed using two mesh levels (coarse 2.1M cells, fine 4.8M cells). GCI estimated at 12.3% for the peak-hemolysis operating point, exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. A third refinement level was not completed due to computational resource constraints. The team judged the discretization error acceptable given the relative comparison nature of the assessment, but the formal GCI criterion is not met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
