      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion and regulatory submission metric.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate is the primary QoI and is identical to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1). The QoI is computed directly from CFD-predicted shear stress histories integrated through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model, consistent with FDA guidance."
    },
